<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
    <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>WZBC Audio Archive</title>
    <meta name="description"
            content="Audio archive of the last two weeks of programming on WZBC Newton 90.1 Boston College Radio">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- Copyright 2008 Tom Worster. ISC license. See readme.txt -->

    <style type="text/css" media="all">
        html, body, div, span, object, iframe, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5,
        h6, p, blockquote, pre, a, abbr, acronym, address, cite, code,
        del, dfn, em, img, ins, kbd, q, samp, strong, sub, sup, tt, var,
        dl, dt, dd, ol, ul, li, fieldset, form, label, legend, table,
        caption, tbody, tfoot, thead, tr, th, td {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            outline: 0;
            font-size: 1em;
        }

        body {
            font-size: 76%;
            font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.28em;
            color: black;
            background: white;
            padding: 2em;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 150%;
        }

        #archivelinks {
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-bottom: 2em;
        }

        #archivelinks td {
            vertical-align: top;
            border-top: 1px solid #999;
            padding: 0.2em 1em 0.2em 0;
        }

        #archivelinks td.space {
            height: 2em;
        }

        #archivelinks td.date {
            font-size: 125%;
            margin-top: 1em;
            padding: 0.5em 1em 1em 0;
        }

        #archivelinks td.ntb {
            border-top: none;
        }

        #archivelinks td.c1 {
            width: 2em;
        }

        #archivelinks td.c2 {
            text-align: right;
            padding-right: 0.5em;
        }

        a {
            color: #400;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: #900;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        p.help {
            font-size: 85%;
            color: #777;
            margin-top: 0.75em;
            width: 60em;
        }

        p.helplink {
            margin: 1em 0 3em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>WZBC Audio Archive</h1>
<p class="helplink"><a href="#help">HELP</a></p>
{pagecontent}
<p><a name="help">HELP</a></p>
<p class="help">The "listen" links are so-called 'M3U playlist' files (small text files containing
    info about the audio) that programs like
    iTunes, QuickTime Player, WinAmp and Window Media Player can open. If your computer
    doesn't play the archive automatically when you click the link you may be able to download
    the file (if it didn't already) and open it in one of those player programs.</p>
<p class="help">Happily, it's normally possible to configure
    your computer so that the links play automatically. But, sadly, I don't have any advice on
    how to do it.</p>
</body>
</html>
